        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued August 28 at 9:15PM MDT by NWS Goodland KS</headline>
        <description>At 915 PM MDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm 4
miles north of Flagler, moving southeast at 15 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 50 mph and nickel size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to outdoor objects is
possible.

This strong thunderstorm will be near...
Flagler around 920 PM MDT.

This includes Interstate 70 in Colorado between mile markers 390 and
418.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
